## Summary

Scroll the Run history card into view when clicking the **History** button on a cron job in the `/cron` page.

Fixes #59902

## Change Type
- [x] Bug fix

## Scope
- [x] UI / DX

## Linked Issue
- Fixes #59902

## Root Cause

The History button at `ui/src/ui/views/cron.ts:1667` only calls `props.onLoadRuns(job.id)` — no scroll, focus, or visual feedback. The Run history card renders below the jobs list (line 627), so with enough jobs it sits below the fold and the click appears to be a no-op.

## What changed

1. Added `data-run-history` attribute to the Run history `<section>` card (line 627) for DOM targeting
2. After `onLoadRuns()`, added `requestAnimationFrame` + `scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "start" })` to bring the card into viewport

## Real behavior proof

**Behavior addressed**: The `/cron` History button loads run data but provides no visual feedback when the Run history card is below the fold.

**Real environment tested**: WSL2 (Ubuntu 22.04), Node v22, upstream `openclaw/openclaw` main. No local OpenClaw dev instance available — verified via source inspection against commit `b25a0d013b64`.

**steps**:
1. Source inspection of `ui/src/ui/views/cron.ts` confirmed History button handler at line 1667 only calls `onLoadRuns(job.id)` with no scroll/focus
2. Confirmed Run history `<section class="card">` at line 627 has no identifying attribute for scroll targeting
3. Added `data-run-history` attribute and `scrollIntoView` call — 2 lines changed, no logic modifications

**evidence**:

Before (current main):
```typescript
@click=${(event: Event) => {
  event.stopPropagation();
  props.onLoadRuns(job.id);
}}
```

After (this patch):
```typescript
@click=${(event: Event) => {
  event.stopPropagation();
  props.onLoadRuns(job.id);
  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    document.querySelector("[data-run-history]")?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "start" });
  });
}}
```

**What was not tested**:
- Live browser UI testing (no local OpenClaw dev environment)
- Maintainer can apply `proof: override` if source-level evidence is sufficient for this minimal UI scroll fix
